text: The 2000 Swale Borough Council election took place on 4 May 2000 to elect members of Swale Borough Council in Kent, England. One third of the council was up for election and the council remained under no overall control. After the election, the composition of the council was *Liberal Democrats 22 *Conservative 15 *Labour 12 ==Election result== ==By-elections between 2000 and 2002== ==References== 2000 Category:2000 English local elections Category:2000s in Kent
